                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">330/9–1852: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Japan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-09-18T18:30:00-04:00"
                            >September 18, 1952—6:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>734. In Sep 18 mtg US rejected <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> charge made
                    Sep 17. <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> in rebuttal continued bitter
                    attack against US. Reiterated Amer colony theme and stated Jap militaristic,
                    citing <persName corresp="#p_YOSHIDAJ1">Yoshida</persName> Aug 4 talk. Final
                    vote 10–1 (<gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>)–0.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ACHESONDG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
